[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T17:52:08+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo collage showing error messages over Congress.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/rL_yxmd2JaSNtFf1noJkvD6BaZE=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73705288/STK461_INTERNET_CHILD_SAFETY_E_Stock_CVirginia.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image:<em> </em>Cath Virginia&nbsp;/ The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Nu7LP8\">The Federal Trade Commission has <a href=\"https://www.ftc.gov/news-events/news/press-releases/2024/11/ftc-order-against-ai-enabled-review-platform-sitejabber-will-ensure-consumers-get-truthful-accurate?utm_campaign=ftc_order_against_ai-enab&amp;utm_content=1730920032&amp;utm_medium=social&amp;utm_source=twitter\">charged Sitejabber</a>, an online review platform, with violating its new fake reviews rules by using point-of-sale reviews to misrepresent what customers think about products. In one of its first enforcement actions under <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/21/24276240/the-ftcs-ru", "id": 1467668, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/6/24289857/ftc-fake-review-order-sitejabber-misleading-product-ratings", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The FTC orders Sitejabber to stop faking product reviews", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T17:48:27+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"New York Times Tech Workers Go On Strike\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/q8DpCC06ZrgIHSoNTlTxbmmxkM4=/0x2:7752x5170/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73705282/2182236802.0.jpg\" />\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"NqiCng\">Striking <em>New York Times</em> tech workers have created <a href=\"https://guild-build.netlify.app\">a \u201cGuild Builds\u201d page</a> dedicated to strike-themed games you can play, including a spin on <em>Wordle, </em>a word search, and the custom <em>Connections</em> I reported on earlier today.</p>\n<p id=\"SdAsdK\">As part of its strike announcement on Monday, the New York Times Tech Guild requested that people don\u2019t cross the digital picket line <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/news/474209/new-york-times-strike-wordle-connections\">to play the <em>NYT\u2019s</em> daily puzzle games</a>. This collection of five other games offers an alternative if you want to support the striking workers but also do some brain teasers. </p>\n<p id=\"Y", "id": 1467669, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/6/24289937/nyt-tech-workers-strike-games-wordle", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "NYT tech workers are making their own games while on strike", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T17:41:46+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of Microsoft\u2019s 2024 Surface Laptop.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/SgZEloZFzmEKaD3GGIyClbXaTRI=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73705270/DSCF7817_Enhanced_NR.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Chris Welch / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"25s7fl\">Microsoft is testing a big Windows on Arm update to let more x64 software and games run under Prism emulation on <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/26/24186432/microsoft-windows-on-arm-qualcomm-copilot-plus-pcs-prism-emulator\">Copilot Plus PC with Qualcomm\u2019s Snapdragon X Elite</a> or X Plus processors. The capability comes as part of the <a href=\"https://blogs.windows.com/windows-insider/2024/11/06/announcing-windows-11-insider-preview-build-27744-canary-channel/\">Windows 11 Insider Preview Build 27744</a>, rolling out to testers in the Canary Channel.</p>\n<p id=\"VOIvAW\">This way, Qualcomm\u2019s new chips can run more kinds of apps that don", "id": 1467670, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/6/24289844/microsoft-windows-on-arm-emulator-prism-update", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Microsoft\u2019s new emulator could bring more games to Windows on Arm", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T16:37:32+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of the Roblox wordmark logo in green\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/bRCLyohiyorX_mS3rJKCBvpENI8=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73705146/STK146_Roblox_New_01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"xQyIgt\">Roblox is going to block kids from accessing certain types of experiences following reports alleging that the platform has enabled child abuse.</p>\n<p id=\"nnpa1V\">One new measure will stop kids under 13 from accessing experiences with \u201ccertain types of interactive features,\u201d Roblox says <a href=\"https://devforum.roblox.com/t/updating-experience-guideline-policies-to-keep-our-younger-users-safe/3249079\">in a post on its developer forum</a>. Those include \u201csocial hangouts,\u201d where the primary purpose is to communicate with others over text or voice chat, and \u201cfree-form 2D user creation\u201d experiences, where players can do things like draw on a chalkb", "id": 1467286, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/6/24289837/roblox-banning-preteens-social-hangout-spaces", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Roblox is banning kids from \u2018social hangout\u2019 spaces", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T16:30:09+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of Samsung\u2019s logo on a black, blue, and aqua background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Ie7TE6juWH9M_HA-RQZhyokuFGE=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73705117/acastro_STK075_02.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"8XxVtL\">Samsung might be working on a \u201cGalaxy S25 Slim\u201d model, with similar rumors to <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/17/24159114/iphone-17-slim-rumor-2025\">the ones about a \u201cSlim\u201d iPhone 17</a> in 2025 <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/24/24205325/slim-iphone-17-rumor-plus-mini\">that may replace the iPhone Plus</a>. <a href=\"https://www.etnews.com/20241031000259\">South Korea\u2019s ET news</a> first reported on it, saying Samsung might release a slim smartphone during the second quarter of 2025 (April \u2013 June) as a follow-up a few months after the rest of the Galaxy S25 family makes their debut. </p>\n<p id=\"FK", "id": 1467287, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/6/24289757/samsung-galaxy-s25-slim-iphone-17-rumor-sm-s937u", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Galaxy S25 \u2018Slim\u2019 rumors suggest a skinny phone showdown next year  ", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T16:07:10+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Evernote\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/kS0UkLpyUl_XA58ZcQpHhIiKA1w=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72872491/jbareham_190314_3294_0011_2.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by James Bareham / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"TqwcK5\">These days, we are all dealing with huge amounts of information, from meeting notes to social media, to photos and videos, to whatever else we\u2019ve collected \u2014 and we are all trying to find some way to store it, organize it, and find it when we need it. </p>\n<p id=\"0roBau\">If you want to get really basic, you can use a spreadsheet or create a simple set of word-processing documents. Otherwise, you can try what is somewhat inaccurately described as a note-taking app. These apps, at their simplest, store your notes and other thoughts and, at their more complex, are capable of manipulating any and all content you want to drop into them. </p>\n<p id=\"RTYSb9\">One of the most ", "id": 1467288, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23942597/notes-text-evernote-onenote-keep-apps", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The best note-taking apps for collecting your thoughts and data", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T14:51:30+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo collage of various brands of noise cancelling headphones.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/EJzyIAPtfAlIO6EhtMh_DjcMkaw=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/67126629/247231_Buying_Guide_Headphones_CVirginia.19.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Get some peace and quiet with any of our top picks for noise-canceling headphones. Sony\u2019s still the best overall, but there are reasons to go elsewhere, too.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/21345733/best-noise-canceling-headphones\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>\n\n", "id": 1466593, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/21345733/best-noise-canceling-headphones", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The best noise-canceling headphones to buy right now", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T14:42:50+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"CLA car in camouflage driving on the track\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6WievepU3vV9okEXQkGsTlgqzjo=/0x0:2515x1677/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73704885/24c0370_001.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The all-electric CLA.</em> | Image: Mercedes-Benz</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"tgHe93\">Mercedes-Benz <a href=\"https://media.mbusa.com/releases/release-13ade706e08532ed28da51676b06c06e-a-closer-look-at-the-upcoming-cla-sporty-design-meets-efficiency\">is showing off its all-electric CLA prototype</a> and sharing a few new details planned for the upcoming 2025 production version. The CEO of Mercedes-Benz Group, Ola K\u00e4llenius, provides a limited tour of the car, in which he talks to its new AI assistant, and takes it for a spin <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2ARBtZa2-gI\">in a new video posted by the automaker</a>.</p>\n<p id=\"oC7fGA\">The CLA is camouflaged like <a href=\"https://www.motorauthority.com/news/114204", "id": 1466594, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/6/24289696/mercedes-benz-cla-prototype-ev-hybrid-tease", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Mercedes-Benz\u2019s electric future starts with this CLA prototype", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T14:29:24+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of Microsoft\u2019s Windows logo\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/3dpqZ_KSWq5lkkDyge5IhWpXABg=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73704858/acastro_STK109_microsoft_02.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Xo4R0w\">Microsoft is adding AI-powered text editing to Notepad, the stripped-down text editor originally <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Windows_Notepad\">introduced in 1983</a>. The feature, <a href=\"https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/use-rewrite-in-notepad-to-enhance-your-writing-with-ai-4088b954-c97b-46dc-813f-959be01746d5\">called Rewrite</a>, is rolling out in preview to Windows Insiders and will let you use AI to \u201crephrase sentences, adjust tone, and modify the length of your content,\u201d according to the <a href=\"https://blogs.windows.com/windows-insider/2024/11/06/new-ai-experiences-for-paint-and-notepad-begin-rolling-ou", "id": 1466595, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/6/24289707/microsoft-notepad-ai-text-editing-rewrite", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Even Microsoft Notepad is getting AI text editing now", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T14:09:52+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"An illustration of the Apple logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/QKjtlPrNgY4Fhk5Rev8lUspXWKE=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73704828/STK071_ACastro_apple_0001.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"haPuET\">Apple has released iOS / iPadOS 18.2 into public beta, as <a href=\"https://www.macrumors.com/2024/11/06/ios-18-2-first-public-beta/?utm_source=dlvr.it&amp;utm_medium=threads\">spotted by <em>MacRumors</em></a>. It includes access to the second wave of Apple Intelligence features that were <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/23/24277811/apple-intelligence-ios-18-2-beta-chatgpt-visual-intelligence-image-generation\">already available to developers</a>, like the AI-generated custom emoji feature Genmoji and the Image Playground feature that generates pictures. </p>\n<p id=\"4nRKhm\">It also adds <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/25/24278716/siri-cha", "id": 1466596, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/6/24289714/ios-18-2-apple-intelligence-public-beta-chatgpt-siri-image-playground", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Apple\u2019s iOS 18.2 public beta starts opening up access to more AI features", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T13:30:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of the Nintendo Switch and Switch Lite on top of a table.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/hSwceis5SXWPP12OuW8TfIoi5W8=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73704744/akrales_190820_3597_0105.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"3if0up\">Nintendo\u2019s next console is going to have a kickass library of games to start. Last night, when there was absolutely <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/6/24289558/in-case-you-missed-it\">nothing else of note happening in the world</a>, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/5/24284745/switch-2-backward-compatibility-nintendo-online-preservation\">Nintendo announced that its still-unannounced Switch successor would be backward-compatible with existing Switch games</a>. The announcement is an early sign that Nintendo might be able to avoid the painful transition between consoles and better unify its g", "id": 1466136, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/6/24289674/nintendo-switch-2-next-generation-backward-compatibility", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Nintendo\u2019s next generation is off to a great start", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T13:08:09+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A picture of Donald Trump in black and white, wearing a ball cap and jacket with a colorful blue, yellow, and green background with large swirly lines.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/iIOMKxiOfh57j2337Zznb_ufNb0=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73704705/VRG_Illo_STK175_L_Normand_DonaldTrump_Positive.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Laura Normand / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"kcGTR7\">Big Tech leaders from across the industry are lining up to congratulate <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/6/24287838/donald-trump-wins-2024-presidential-election\">Donald Trump on his victory</a> in the US presidential election. Trump has butted heads with many of the executives now <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/31/24282719/tech-leaders-trump-jeff-bezos-zuckerberg-pichai\">cozying up to the soon-to-be president</a>, who recently threatened to throw Meta CEO Mark Zuckerberg in prison and <a hre", "id": 1466137, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/6/24289649/big-tech-leaders-donald-trump-presidential-election", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "All the Big Tech leaders congratulating Donald Trump", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T13:00:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot from the video game Life is Strange: Double Exposure.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Rpv8j4tp_Df5gYwPfb-43jCXdxE=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73704667/ss_5f78d1dedaf261f256a53bf7e72270f41f824b29.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Square Enix</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>The game\u2019s final episode also teases a larger Life is Strange universe to come.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24289524/life-is-strange-double-exposure-review-pc-ps5-xbox\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>\n\n", "id": 1466138, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24289524/life-is-strange-double-exposure-review-pc-ps5-xbox", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Life is Strange: Double Exposure ends with a disappointing finale", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T11:16:21+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of electric vehicles charging\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/N80K2TOxOF7VVhFbbBibCSd1KHs=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73704507/STK437_Electric_Vehicle_charge_EV.5.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Hugo Herrera / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"iL1JtA\">On the campaign trail, Donald Trump said <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24279434/presidential-election-trump-biden-harris-ev-2024-electric-vehicle-car\">a lot of things about electric vehicles</a>. He said he would \u201cend the electric vehicle mandate on day one,\u201d that EVs \u201cdon\u2019t work,\u201d and that they benefit China and Mexico while hurting American autoworkers. </p>\n<p id=\"M4BlO7\">But he has also <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/21/24202062/elon-musk-donald-trump-endorsement-tesla-ev-tax-credit\">closely aligned himself with Elon Musk</a>, who runs the biggest EV company in the US. And he will likely have Musk continuing to wh", "id": 1465295, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/6/24289494/trump-election-electric-vehicle-tax-credit-tesla-elon-musk", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "What does Trump\u2019s election mean for EVs, Tesla, and Elon Musk?", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T10:49:41+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Google Pixel Watch 3 resting in an orange case box surrounded by other colorful boxes.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/roPzrTEmmnUu98jzSMo40Bnpdqs=/0x0:2700x1800/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73704437/247234_Pixel_Watch_3_AKrales_0189.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Google\u2019s Pixel Watch 3 is an excellent upgrade over its predecessor, with a wealth of new fitness features and smarts.</em> | Image: Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"GhKWc7\">If you thought you needed to wait until Black Friday to score a steep discount on the new <strong>Google Pixel Watch 3</strong>, we\u2019ve got some good news: right now, Wellbots is giving readers of <em>The Verge </em>an exclusive $75 discount, dropping the wearable down to a new all-time low price until November 12th. The 41mm, Wi-Fi-enabled configuration starts at <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2", "id": 1465296, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/6/24288785/googles-pixel-watch-3-m2-macbook-air-deal-sale", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Google\u2019s Pixel Watch 3 is available at a new record low price for Verge\u00a0readers\u00a0 ", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T10:32:25+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A bunch of USB-C chargers on a green backdrop\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/o3U4xyNCiFeeVy6NRu_LwKoiM-c=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73704407/vlad-savov-computex-usb-c-2.0.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Vlad Savov / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"UVXkSK\">You can now buy a USB-C charger that finally hits the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/circuitbreaker/2021/5/25/22453936/usb-c-power-delivery-extended-power-range-epr\">promised power spec</a> for beefy laptops at a max rate of 240W. You probably do not need <a href=\"https://www.mouser.com/ProductDetail/Delta-Electronics/ADP-240KB-BA?qs=i8QVZAFTkqQOWRm1%252BUmOUA%3D%3D\">this charger</a>, and you may not have a device that even supports its peak power, but it\u2019s here now if you want one to future-proof your office setup.</p>\n<p id=\"AEvPUK\">Delta Electronics\u2019 ADP-240KB charger is an AC power supply that supports the <a href=\"https://ww", "id": 1464841, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/6/24289498/delta-electronics-240w-usb-c-pd-charger-first-adapter", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Here\u2019s the first 240W USB-PD charger you can actually buy", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T10:02:17+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Graphic photo illustration of Donald Trump.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6VSFsCdVJMjgr5a3vEGSt895w44=/20x0:2021x1334/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73704362/STK466_ELECTION_2024_CVirginia_E.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Cath Virginia / The Verge | Photos from Scott Olson, Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"pt1YH2\">Donald Trump clinched a presidential victory, ushering in another term of environmental rollbacks that\u2019ll make it more difficult to safeguard our air, water, and climate. </p>\n<p id=\"v77aZ3\">\u201cEnvironmental [regulation] is the biggest tool for stopping growth ... it costs much more to do things environmentally clean,\u201d Trump said in a rambling <a href=\"https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2024-election/trump-records-3-hour-podcast-interview-joe-rogan-rcna177288\">three-hour interview</a> with Joe Rogan on October 25th, when he <a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2019/06/19/climate/us-air-polluti", "id": 1464842, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/6/24288965/election-trump-president-environment-pollution-climate-change", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Another Trump presidency is literally toxic \u2014 his opponents are gearing up for battle ", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T10:00:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Graphic collage of various tech products for sale during Black Friday and Cyber Monday.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/34PpCUfFqfk99i3Nb5yLmPZ7sow=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73700761/247350_CMBF_PACKAGE_ART_CVirginia_LEDE_2040x1360.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p class=\"p--has-dropcap\" id=\"lujmaC\">These days, Black Friday isn\u2019t so much a single-day shopping holiday as it is an ever-expanding, monthslong event that often begins as early as October. The 24-hour deal blitz that once was the focus of newspaper headlines and mobs outside of stores is no more, which makes knowing when and where you should be spending your cash all the more confusing.</p>\n<p id=\"fb5Z1g\">Luckily, we\u2019re here to help. Over the next month or so, we\u2019ll be poring through scores of presale spreadsheets and thousands upon thousands of deals to separate the real discounts fr", "id": 1464843, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24288220/black-friday-best-deals-guide-cyber-monday-tech-gadgets-2024", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Verge\u2019s guide to Black Friday 2024", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T09:30:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Screenshot from a Verge hands-on video with Apple\u2019s new Macs, including the 2024 Mac Mini, the bottom of which is shown here.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ls9gInQNpdjKzykfbBgtDjLMhm8=/0x0:1119x746/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73704274/Screenshot_2024_11_04_at_5.42.35_PM.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Mac Mini power button got you down? Try a power schedule!</em> | Screenshot: YouTube</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"jIHizn\">Apple\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/30/24283861/apple-redesigned-mac-mini-macbook-pro-imac-m4-photos\">new Mac Mini</a> looks like someone hit the Mac Studio with a shrink ray, and I love it. But there is at least one, uh, <em>hot-button</em> issue: you have to reach underneath it to power it on. If that bothers you (and you\u2019re not into flipping it upside down so it looks like it\u2019s wearing a little hat), you can automate when it starts up and shuts down by creating a power schedul", "id": 1464471, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24288127/mac-power-schedule-terminal-commands-automation-startup-shutdown", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How to schedule your Mac to start up and shut down on its own", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T09:23:42+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/c0cnP3_mH8cZCk-GHw9tBkvX8NU=/880x0:6160x3520/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73704262/ST3_Production_Still_4.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Netflix</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"5nvZD8\">We still don\u2019t have a firm premiere date, but <a href=\"https://x.com/netflix/status/1854161874201325856\">Netflix has officially confirmed</a> that the fifth \u2014 and final \u2014 season of <em>Stranger Things</em> will start streaming next year. Aside from that, the streamer <a href=\"https://www.netflix.com/tudum/articles/the-title-of-stranger-things-season-5-episode-1-revealed\">also released the titles</a> for all eight episodes in the new season, which might provide some hints as to what to expect:</p>\n<ul>\n<li id=\"J1XoVO\">Episode 1 - \u201cThe Crawl\u201d</li>\n<li id=\"TIztWP\">Episode 2 - \u201cThe Vanishing of \u2026\u201d (note: this one is intentionally left incomplete, presumably for spoiler reasons)</li>\n<li id=\"T58FR3\">Epi", "id": 1464472, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/6/24289501/stranger-things-season-5-2025-netflix", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Netflix confirms Stranger Things season 5 is coming in 2025", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T09:00:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"AMD\u2019s Ryzen 7 9800X3D processor\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/JdFtMaIXO43GQnwHRkLSXLoyy0A=/0x0:2700x1800/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73704182/247357_AMD_Ryzen_7_9800X3D_TWarren_0002.0.jpg\" />\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>AMD\u2019s 7800X3D successor is also better at non-gaming workloads this time around.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/6/24288948/amd-ryzen-7-9800x3d-review-cpu-processor-benchmark-test\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>\n\n", "id": 1464474, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/6/24288948/amd-ryzen-7-9800x3d-review-cpu-processor-benchmark-test", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "AMD Ryzen 7 9800X3D: the best gaming CPU", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T09:00:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/5LokbwwC2jSZzO9iFKsRmbWClsc=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73704170/acastro_180927_1777_lyft_0003.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"qUWHPA\">Lyft is teaming up with a trio of autonomous driving startups as it races to keep up with Uber, which has also struck a number of deals to put robotaxis on its platform. </p>\n<p id=\"rLt1uX\">Today, the ridehail company said it was teaming up with three different autonomous driving companies: Mobileye, May Mobility, and Nexar. Mobileye and May Mobility plan on deploying autonomous vehicles on Lyft\u2019s network, while Nexar, which makes smart dash cams, will work with Lyft on using its \u201cvideo telematics to create data-driven solutions that accelerate the deployment of AV technologies.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"h5aUzt\">Nexar said it has \u201cover 45 petabytes of real-world footage, spanning 20", "id": 1464473, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/6/24289475/lyft-may-mobility-mobileye-nexar-autonomous-robotaxi", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Lyft is also partnering with robotaxi companies", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T08:00:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/sNT0nBYeXQuABMoIRIyj9kYaSJ0=/0x0:3200x2133/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73704057/goggles_n3.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The DJI Goggles N3 headset, DJI Neo drone, and RC Motion 3 controller.</em> | Photo: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"UjRUwc\">I\u2019m hoping DJI\u2019s affordable new FPV goggles will <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/17/24272736/these-leaked-dji-goggles-n3-could-be-the-missing-puzzle-piece\">be the missing puzzle piece</a> \u2014 a way to cheaply buy <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/8/25/23311957/dji-avata-fpv-drone-goggles-2-price-release-date-preview\">the \u201cIt feels like I\u2019m flying!\u201d experience I had with the DJI Avata</a> for maybe $400 or $500 tops, rather than the current $800 to $1,000 you might have to pay. </p>\n<p id=\"0veRc1\">See, the company announced its budget <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24236503/dji-neo-vs-hoverair-selfie-drone-specs-pr", "id": 1464048, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24285651/dji-goggles-n3-price-release-date-hands-on", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "I flew DJI\u2019s $199 drone with its new $229 Goggles N3", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T07:04:47+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"iPhone 16 in blue and iPhone 16 Plus in pink.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/uAEaNuRjd50wewtpqyM6FDcpDrs=/0x0:2000x1333/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73703986/DSC08407.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo: Allison Johnson / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"QmtrGC\">The European Commission has opened a <a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/commission/presscorner/detail/en/ip_24_5681\">formal investigation</a> into Corning to determine whether it has broken antitrust rules with its dominant Gorilla Glass product. Corning\u2019s Alkali-aluminosilicate glass is used to protect most of the top phones and tablets, with both Samsung and Apple using it extensively across their range of devices. The EU is concerned that Corning has used a variety of exclusivity contracts to exclude rival glass makers from the phone market.</p>\n<p id=\"s8oFnt\">\u201cIt is very frustrating and costly experience to break a mobile phone screen. Therefore, stro", "id": 1463700, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/6/24289450/corning-eu-antitrust-investigation-gorilla-glass", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Corning\u2019s Gorilla Glass under EU antitrust investigation", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-06T06:31:22+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo collage of an image of Donald Trump behind a graphic, glitchy design.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/k2ArZOOhvoWU-hQ9N-UKRSDAJOM=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73703932/STK175_DONALD_TRUMP_CVIRGINIA_D.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge; Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"dwTXTj\">Donald Trump has been declared the winner of the 2024 presidential election. Trump, who <a href=\"https://www.cnn.com/2022/11/15/politics/trump-2024-presidential-bid/index.html\">announced his reelection campaign in 2022</a>, is the second president in US history to be elected to two nonconsecutive terms. Trump <a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2024/11/06/us/politics/trump-victory-speech.html?smid=url-share\">declared victory</a> early on Wednesday, followed by <a href=\"https://apnews.com/projects/election-results-2024/\">the AP</a>, <a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/live/2024/11/06/us/trump-", "id": 1463701, "language": null, "link": "https://www.